episodes.title: Never Cry Shitwolf
episodes.plot: After spending another 8 months behind bars, Julian, Mr. Lahey and Randy are released. They are surprised when Ricky is the new supervisor of Sunnyvale.

episodes.title: A Man's Gotta Eat
episodes.plot: Rickys term as Supervisor has left Julian with no trailer and illegal business in his name. Randy and Lahey have difficulties in their new life, which forces Randy to return to prostitution. Bubbles and Ricky unveil their fields to Julian.

episodes.title: Rub n Tiz'zug
episodes.plot: The Boys end up attacking each other due to a misunderstanding. The Boys make Cory and Trevor steal furniture. Julian decides to use their trailers for a 'rub-n-tug'. The girls that they get for the massage parlor are Cyrus's girls.

episodes.title: The Green Bastard
episodes.plot: Ricky decides to hold a community day in the park, alongside Lahey's acceptance of a trailer park supervisor award. The community day also gives Bubbles a chance to become his wrestling alter-ego, the Green Bastard from parts unknown.

episodes.title: Conky
episodes.plot: Bubble has a toothache but refuses to go to the hospital without his puppet, Conky. But Ricky and Julian threw him away, so now they must find him.

episodes.title: If You Love Something, Set It Free
episodes.plot: Something in the night attacks the boys while they're working their pot field.

episodes.title: Propane, Propane
episodes.plot: Some marriage proposals create turmoil between Ricky, the Laheys, and Randy.

episodes.title: Workin' Man
episodes.plot: The boys race to harvest their pot field before the cops find it. Meanwhile, Lahey drifts into insanity.

episodes.title: Dear Santa Claus: Go Fuck Yourself
episodes.plot: It's a flashback to Christmas, 1997. Julian gives Ricky the car he'll have for years. The origin of Lahey and Randy's relationship is revealed. Julian, Ricky and some crowbars go Christmas shopping.
